  "id": "MAL-2026-5427",
  "summary": "Malicious code in @payment-review/store (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (16277824e707bfa5d164fe338408172b64a7e3c02ee6669b1391b8ad1ae41965)\nOn `npm install`, the package's `preinstall` hook (`scripts.preinstall: node index.js || true`) executes index.js, which collects `os.hostname()`, `os.userInfo().username`, `__dirname`, `process.cwd()`, and the package name, JSON-stringifies and hex-encodes the payload, and exfiltrates it via two channels: (1) a DNS lookup whose label encodes the payload under a subdomain of `oast.live` (Interactsh out-of-band canary infrastructure), and (2) an HTTP POST to bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. The `|| true` suffix masks errors so the install appears to succeed even if the beacon fails. The package is published under a generic `@payment-review/store` scope at version 99.0.1 with description `security research` — the canonical dependency-confusion shape targeting an internal `payment-review` namespace. There is no advertised functionality; the install-time beacon is the package's only effect.\n",
